node.text:
☕️ Sumatra, Java, and Sulawesi are familiar to coffee lovers, named for the Indonesian islands on which the beans are grown. #TraderJoes Indonesia Bali Kintamani Small Lot Coffee gives you a big taste of how well beans from the smaller island of #Bali compare with their neighbors.
•
The #Kintamani area of northern Bali sits in the shadow of Mt. #Batur, an active volcano, which has lent its influence over the years to develop rich soils in the region. Combine this arable earth with a humid tropical climate, and you can grow some truly stunning coffee beans!
•
Farmers hand-pick the 100% Arabica #coffee cherries and wet-process them, removing the outer hull before drying the beans. This approach yields a cup that is fuller-bodied, with reduced acidity. Each sip is bold—yet smooth & balanced, with notes of zesty orange peel, vanilla, and sweet dried fruit. 
—
• Beans from Bali, Indonesia 🇮🇩• Medium Roast •
• 71mg Caffeine Per 6 fl. oz. Cup • Limited •

node.text:
Strolling down a Seoul street, you’ll encounter vendors cooking sweet, stuffed pancakes. Strolling down our frozen aisle, you’ll encounter #TraderJoes Sweet Cinnamon Filled #KoreanPancakes—ready to take home, heat, and eat!
•
Our version of traditional #hotteok is made with wheat and rice flours and stuffed with a cinnamon-spiked, sweet-potato filling. The cooked dough is flaky & chewy (reminiscent of mochi), with a luscious, #cinnamon-y center.
•
They’re best enjoyed tolerably hot, right after cooking in an ungreased pan (or microwave, or air fryer). Make one your especially indulgent #breakfast. Or slice one laterally and fill with a scoop of TJ’s French Vanilla Ice Cream for a decadent #dessert sandwich!
—
• Product of Republic of Korea 🇰🇷• 12.7 oz. Pkg. of Four •

node.text:
📷: Just a very small “taste” of the #Pumpkin products that start showing up in our stores tomorrow!
—
It’s (finally) time. You’ve waited. You’ve wondered. Your patience is about to be rewarded big time, because…#PumpkinSeason is here!
•
New products & returning faves are arriving every day, throughout the season. Some are in stores now, some will hit shelves this week, and some will be available in the weeks ahead—meaning every trip to #TraderJoes will be a visit filled with discovery, wonder… and #pumpkins!
•
👉🏽 Which fall products are you most excited about?

node.text:
🔦 SEPTEMBER SPOTLIGHT CHEESE: #TraderJoes Canestrato Pepato Sardinian Sheep’s Milk Cheese with Black Peppercorns • Link in Bio for more info •
—
“Sardinian Sheep’s Milk Cheese” has a magical ring to it. Not surprisingly, the magic continues far beyond the title of this September #SpotlightCheese! Pasteurized sheep’s milk meets proprietary cultures and whole #peppercorns to yield a #cheese with positive distinction.
•
It’s semi-hard, with an underlying rich, nutty flavor; pleasantly piquant notes; and the occasional peppery crunch. Pair it with a #PaleAle. Grate it over any pasta, or into #risotto. Its creamy-peppery character will make your homemade #CacioePepe magical, indeed!
—
• Limited • Product of Italy 🇮🇹 • Animal Rennet •
• Available through September while supplies last •

node.text:
📷: “Positively Plantain Snack Mix,” featuring #TraderJoes Plantain Croutons • #TJsRecipe Link In Bio •
—
Croutons are like icing on the cake! (Except, they are not sweet and usually on salad.) Anyway, there are a few reasons we think our Plantain Croutons are as exciting as icing…
•
One, they’re made from #plantains instead of bread. Two, accordingly, they’re #glutenfree. Three, these crispy, crunchy, cubed #Croutons are seasoned with garlic & sea salt, creating a mighty tasty profile.
•
Beyond #salads, you can scatter some on #soups, or scramble them with your eggs. And like our #PlantainChips, these Croutons make a great stand-alone snack… or mixed up with a bunch of your other favorite TJ’s tidbits.
—
• Gluten Free • Vegan • Product of Ecuador 🇪🇨•

node.text:
📷: TJ’s Rosemary Sfogliette Crackers & Red Pepper Spread with Eggplant & Garlic •
—
#Sfogliatelle [sfow-lee-ah-TELL-ee] is a puff-style pastry from the #Campania region of southern Italy, surrounding Naples. It’s popular for its stacked layers of very thin “leaves,” which create a crisp, delicate texture that’s typically filled with some kind of cream. 
•
On one visit to that region, we encountered Sfogliette [sfow-lee-EH-tee], which is a #snack cracker with attributes similar to its pastry relative—but with a savory profile. This was the inspiration for #TraderJoes Sfogliette Crackers.
•These thin, hexagonal #crackers are made from wheat & rice flours, baked with olive oil, and seasoned with dried #rosemary & sea salt. Their crunchy character, with aromas and flavors of rosemary & olive oil, make them ideal to munch on alone, or with thin slices of your favorite #cheese. 
—
• Product of Italy 🇮🇹• 140 Calories Per 12 Crackers •

node.text:
We’ve found that the average jerky is often dry, tough to chew, and overwhelmingly salty. Luckily, #TraderJoes Original #TurkeyJerky is not your “average” jerky!
•
Since 2007, we’ve sold this popular #snack that’s made with natural* turkey raised without added hormones, using a recipe that includes sugar (5g per serving), soy sauce, apple cider vinegar, salt, paprika, and natural smoke flavoring. 
•
It’s #highprotein (11g per one-ounce serving) and #lowfat (0g per serving), with a moist, slightly chewy (but not tough) texture. And it has just the right balance of salt & sweet! It’s one of the best #jerky companions for #camping, #hiking, flights, lunches, emergency kits...
—
• 4 oz. Re-sealable Pouch • No Nitrates or Added MSG • 
*natural = no artificial ingredients & minimally processed

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trader Joe's on September 01, 2021. May be an image of food and drink.

node.text:
📷: “Spiked Strawberry Lemonade,” featuring #TraderJoes Kentucky Bourbon Straight Whiskey • #TJsRecipe Link In Bio •
—
🥃 Many who embraced baking back in 2020 learned first-hand the way sourdough starter passes on its unique characteristics from loaf to loaf. Likewise, if you became a #Bourbon bootlegger last year (a decidedly smaller crowd), you’ve learned how leftover sour mash (grain, malt, water) passes on the best qualities from batch to batch.
•
In the case of our Kentucky Bourbon #StraightWhiskey, those qualities include sweet, fruity, spicy notes, and hints of oak and brown sugar. The finish is long and dry, with lingering vanilla notes that make it super for sipping neat. Whether you’re making a Manhattan, #MintJulip, or #OldFashioned, you’ll appreciate the real value of this private label spirit.
—
• Distilled in Bardstown, KY • TJ’s where spirits are sold •
• Aged 5 yrs. (minimum) in new, charred oak barrels •

node.text:
Some people drink TJ’s Organic Raw Apple Cider Vinegar daily as a home remedy—which made us think: if you’re going to drink #applecidervinegar, why not make it enjoyable and fun? That’s one of the ideas behind #TraderJoes Organic Sparkling Apple Cider Vinegar Beverages!
•
These 12 fluid-ounce cans contain a snappy, refreshing mix of carbonated water, organic apple juice concentrate, and organic lemon juice concentrate—plus a full tablespoon of apple cider vinegar. Each one is further flavor-enhanced with either organic #strawberry juice concentrate (red can), or organic #ginger juice (green).
•
👉🏾 Tell us: which Cider you on? 🍎 Lemon + Strawberry,
or 🍏 Ginger + Lemon?
—
• Organic • Kosher • 35 Calories Per Can •
• Color From Fruit & Vegetable Juice •

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trader Joe's on August 30, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text:
We sell a lot of #brioche in our stores—and you might say that #challah is like braided brioche. (Granted, #TraderJoes Holiday Challah is more like the spiral hairstyle of a certain space princess.) The presence of eggs and sugar in both recipes is the connection, while the main difference is the use of oil (instead of butter) in the Challah.
•
Ultimately, the baked result is very similar: yellow-hued crumb that is soft, moist, and mildly sweet. Whether you’re enjoying it as part of your religious tradition—or simply because you can’t get enough of the ‘bread-just-short-of-cake’ profile—we’ve got your #loaves. Find them on our #bakery shelves for a limited time in September!
—
• 20 oz. Spiral Loaf • Kosher (pareve) • Limited •

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trader Joe's on August 27, 2021. May be an image of fruit and indoor.

node.text:
🥯 #TraderJoes Vegan Cream Cheese Alternative makes the joy of a toasted bagel & schmear reality for the #dairyfree crowd. And while its name may be more practical than inspired—the character of this #vegancheese is nothing, if not inspired!
•
Our skilled supplier combines coconut oil, chickpea protein, and potato starch to create a base that looks, feels, and spreads like creamy cheese. The right amount of yeast extract and salt produces that lightly tart, #creamcheese flavor that lights up lactose lovers—while remaining #lactosefree.
•
Use it like regular cream cheese... on #bagels, of course, with or without some TJ’s #SmokedSalmon. Create a cream-cheese-like #frosting for cupcakes, or make an easy #vegandip by mixing it with your favorite TJ’s seasoning or hot sauce.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trader Joe's on August 26, 2021. May be an image of succotash.

node.text:
📷: #TraderJoes Soyaki sauce with white fish on a bed of TJ’s Soycutash •
—
#Soyaki, as its name suggests, is our riff on #teriyaki sauce... and it’s a tasty riff! The base is soy sauce and cane sugar, with fresh garlic & ginger purées. But what really sets this sauce apart is the presence of sesame, both in the form of toasted sesame oil and #sesameseeds.
•
In addition to flavor, the seeds contribute a nice texture to this sweet & tangy sauce, setting it up for a variety of uses… It’s a ready #marinade for #grilledchicken or baked fish. How about Soyaki shrimp #stirfry? And since it’s #vegan, it’s well-matched with baked #tofu or roasted vegetables. It even makes a great #dippingsauce for any of the #Gyoza you find in our freezers!
